Castelluccio began his career as an actor in 1986. Some of his film credits include ''[[Made (2001 film)|Made]]'' with Jon Favreau, ''Fire'' with Robert Klein and ''[[Diary of a Hitman]]'' with [[Danny Aiello]]. In television, Federico's credits include ''[[NYPD Blue]]'' and his best known role in the HBO hit series, ''[[The Sopranos]]'', as the [[Naples|Neapolitan]] enforcer [[Furio Giunta]].
